scene.message:
Aki: Aaah!! Damn it~{nl}
I'll tell Papa on you!{nl}
Papa is strong, you know!{waitkey}{clearbox}He'll finish off the lot{nl}
of you in one shot!!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Daa-hahaha!{nl}
We just did what anyone{nl}
would. No thanks needed!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Honestly, no number of{nl}
lives would be enough.{waitkey}Not that telling you{nl}
does any good.{waitkey}{ret}

Yosuke: I'm really grateful.{nl}
By the way... there's someone{nl}
I'd like you to meet.{waitkey}Could you come with me?{waitkey}{ret}

Yosuke: He's someone who's{nl}
looked after me since I came{nl}
here, and he believed me.{waitkey}{clearbox}Right now he's looking into{nl}
the two worlds and such.{nl}
He may have found something.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Ohh~ He actually took{nl}
you seriously, huh.{nl}
Just what kind of guy is he?{waitkey}{ret}

Yosuke: Well, that's...{nl}
you'll see when you meet him.{nl}
I'll wait in the library!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: What's gotten into him?{nl}
Well, in any case,{nl}
let's head to the library.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: H-hey! Aw, man,{nl}
he's already gone.{nl}
Is that guy really hurt?{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: ...{wait_fr:60}Fine, fine!{nl}
You jerk, Inaba!{nl}
Masao monkey! Monkey monkey!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Ah! Why you!{nl}
You said monkey just now!{nl}
You said Masao!{waitkey}Don't call me by that{nl}
lame name!{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Cut it out, you two!{nl}
Come on, {ctl07:1},{nl}
let's get to the library.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: H-hey...{nl}
He hopped off on one foot.{waitkey}Should we go check it out?{nl}
Eh, Reiji?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Geez~!{nl}
You're such a buzzkill.{nl}
Lighten up a little, will ya.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: I wonder if he's the{nl}
one Yosuke meant. If so,{nl}
he's surely in the library.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: ...{wait_fr:60}That girl calls{nl}
Kandori her father, but{nl}
is she really his child?{waitkey}I've never heard he had{nl}
a child.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: That brat from before{nl}
really ticks me off!{nl}
Next time, she'll get it.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Geez, that Ayase's{nl}
got such a mouth on her.{waitkey}And yet some guys go for{nl}
that type. The world's a{nl}
mystery.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: That Reiji's a real{nl}
twisted-up guy.{waitkey}Hey, you and me, let's{nl}
do something about him.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: ...{wait_fr:60}Naito too{nl}
has lost someone dear{nl}
to him... It must be hard...{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Kids can be{nl}
surprisingly cruel, y'know.{nl}
They don't know when to stop.{waitkey}{clearbox}What if someone died, huh?{wait_fr:88}{nl}
Oh, she means to kill from{nl}
the start, so I guess it's{nl}
fine? Wahaha!{waitkey}Ooh, scary...{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: I wanna go home soon~{nl}
If not for this, I'd be{nl}
grooving at a club right now.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Come to think of it...{nl}
where did everyone in this{nl}
world go?{waitkey}{clearbox}You were here too, {ctl07:1},{nl}
and Inaba, and everyone.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: It looks no different{nl}
at all, and yet they call{nl}
it another world.{waitkey}{ret}

Hiremon Stone.{nl}
A massive rock unearthed in{nl}
1963 during the school's{nl}
original construction.{waitkey}{clearbox}Its makeup is samataite,{nl}
but magnetic anomalies{nl}
have been detected.{waitkey}{clearbox}Legend says a heavenly{nl}
being named Hiremon{waitkey}cast it down from the sky{nl}
as a guardian stone for{nl}
Mikage Town.{waitkey}{ret}
